_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":true,"pe_now":5.4,"pe_percentile":5.0,"median_pe":11.7,"earnings_yield_pct":18.52,"pb":0.73,"ev_ebitda":null,"quality_score":62.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":15.4,"peg":0.35,"cheapness":{"status":"good","read":"P/E at the 5-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 cheap vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 5.4\u00d7 earnings for ~15% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22480.35\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business is a trap, not a bargain.","why_it_can_fail":"P/E breaks for loss-makers / one-offs; for banks use P/B not EV/EBITDA; a multiple cheap vs history can stay cheap if the business has structurally de-rated."},"ownership":{"ok":true,"na":null,"holders":{"Promoter":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[45.24,45.24,45.24,45.24,45.24,45.24,45.24,45.24,45.24,45.24,45.24,45.24],"latest_pct":45.24,"chg_1y_pp":0.0},"FII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[17.15,21.21,21.91,22.59,23.19,21.95,21.24,21.55,20.25,20.17,20.36,21.39],"latest_pct":21.39,"chg_1y_pp":-0.16},"DII":{"periods":["Jun 2023","Sep 2023","Dec 2023","Mar 2024","Jun 2024","Sep 2024","Dec 2024","Mar 2025","Jun 2025","Sep 2025","Dec 2025","Mar 2026"],"values":[25.03,21.51,21.76,21.99,21